Context:
Topics covered in the stress management group at George Brown College include Stress and the Brain, Self Care, Stress and Our Thoughts, Perfectionism and Procrastination, Imposter Phenomenon, and Social Health, Isolation, and Stress. The group is open for anyone to join on a first-come, first-served basis. Interested individuals need to fill out a form to join. For more information about other wellness skill-building groups and college news, applicants can sign up. The contact details provided are 416-415-2000 (voice) and 1-877-515-5559 (TTY), and ask.george@georgebrown.ca for queries. The college's social media hub can also be visited for additional information.

Please note that the information provided on the website is subject to change without notice, and students should verify George Brown College fee requirements.
